Text.Value: These two outsiders are threatening me, Ikaron.
Do you really want to take a beating over some jewellery?
DO AS HE SAYS, OR JOIN THE SNAKEBITTEN GIRL IN HER GRAVE.
Thieving children wind up dead around here. Do as he says.
And stay down.
You're sick.
He's an orphan. How'd you like it if I struck you?
Better do what he says, boy. There's already one thief to bury today.
Maybe you will. But personally, I doubt it.
You're not fooling anyone, boy. Why'd you take it?
You're sick.
Probably not. It's just tin and glass.
Meddlers are even worse than thieves. You're not meddling, are you?
I tried to give you a chance. You're on your own.
Is this true?
We were wrong to trust you. I see that now.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: | Tiefling moves to the adventurer | SCRIPTING: Ikaron steps towards Barth

Text.Value: Let us find balance. The child will return the locket - and the adult will act his age.
Sisters! Brothers! To arms!
Fine! It's just tin and glass anyway.
And you, get out of my sight.
There. Don't know why you cared so much. It's junk.
Go, child.
You're not wrong. I wish you were.
Do it, you gutless stinksack!
Theft and revenge have already killed a child here. Calm yourselves - explain what happened.
A beating, huh? Oh no. Whatever will I do?

EditorData.AnimationTags: BARTH clenches fist and stares down the CHILD. He raises his right hand and backslaps the kid, causing the CHILD to stumble. The LOCKET tumbles to the floor and BARTH, seeing this, reaches down to pick it up., Full sequence to be used over several nodes [CodyM]
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: |*The adventurer stares down at the defiant child, wavering, fists clenching*|

Text.Value: And now you're threatening me? You fool.
And I... huh. Someone stole it from me. That's kind of funny.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Angrily feeling his pouches, then confusion.

Text.Value: Keep it, kid. You need it more than me.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Long beat from Barth. His expression changes from surprise to an understanding sadness before he speaks.
EditorData.NodeContext: Long beat. Gruffly. His mother gave him the amulet.

Text.Value: I think it would benefit everyone to calm down here. What happened?
Don't you tell me to calm down - my locket was stolen!
Good, that's settled. Now, disperse.
Just give it back, boy. You're better than this.
Only going to ask you one more time, boy. Hand over my locket.
Good. Everyone happy?
Gods, don't bleed over the thing. It's just tin and glass.
You like watching people hit kids? You happy now?

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Kid turns to the player, angry.

Text.Value: Child, learn your lesson and be grateful.
Whatever you do to the child, I'll repay ten-fold.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Should be Paladin tagged when tag is available.

Text.Value: You're the one making threats - to a child. Pull yourself together.
Can't thank you enough.
Raise a hand to that child and you'll lose it. Your choice.
Quiet. Child, go.
Strike the child, go on. See what happens.
I get my locket back and you'll have no trouble from me.
I want an answer - why'd you steal it?
The boy's a thief.
Fine, lumpy. You win.
Of... of course not.
Just a misunderstanding. The boy was about to give Barth his locket back.
I'm the one looking out for the boy.
But my locket!
I don't have your ugly locket. I've never even seen it before!
What kind of question is that? Why does anyone steal anything?
The boy stole my locket!
Fine. It's worthless anyway.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: |Cinematic Node: Meli stares up at Barth in shock, then down at his hands. He turns and runs.|
EditorData.NodeContext: Meli stares up at Barth in shock, then down at his hands. He turns and runs.|

Text.Value: These little devils get away with everything because of coddling bastards like you.
Feel better? Or were you hoping I'd cry?
Yeah? I'll give you something to laugh about.
What's happening here?

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: |Cinematic Node: Long beat from Barth. His expression changes from surprise to an understanding sadness.|

Text.Value: No idea. This man just started attacking the boy.
Not bad. Not even a little bit bad.
Help! This human is trying to kill me!
Good. You heard them, child. You're free to go.
And both of you thought striking the child was a suitable punishment?
It looked like my mother's, all right?
That bauble worth a thrashing?
My coin's on the tiefling. He looks angry.

Text.Value: And I thought he was a coward.
I said I don't have it. Maybe he dropped it running away from those big, scary goblins.
And you? You had this coming.
You threatening me?
Let the boy take it as a warning - he's getting off lightly.
And that justifies threatening a child?

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: | A nearby guard notices the kid is in trouble.|

Text.Value: To impress a girl, most like.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: SCRIPT: Sticks his tongue out at the adventurer and runs off.|

Text.Value: There's no locket. This bastard's just throwing his weight around.
Guards! This human is trying to hurt me and my friend!
Forget it. I don't want any trouble.
You better do what he says, boy.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: | The kid's screaming catches the attention of a nearby guard. |

Text.Value: Kid's lucky you were here.
Here, take it. Not sure why you care so much about it, honestly.

EditorData.AnimationTags: *DUPE* [TIEFLING CHILD] Gives object to adult <EllenG> [BARTH] takes object from child <EllenG>

Text.Value: He's a thief. Is it any wonder people think that of us all?
I kill meddlers. ARE YOU MEDDLING?
I like meddlers - they make funny noises when I smash them. Are you a meddler?
Nobody's hurting the boy - he's free to leave when he wants.
Fine. I have the stupid amulet. Take it.
Don't you dare lay a finger on that child.
For the last time, I don't have the stupid thing!

EditorData.AnimationTags: [BARTH] raises fist to hit the child <EllenG>

Text.Value: Just warning. I've dealt with your type before, human.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: | *The kid's screaming goes unnoticed. The kid wavers.* |

Text.Value: Scram before I give you something to care about.

EditorData.NodeContext: Kid runs away at end of node.

Text.Value: You raise a hand to me, it'd better have steel in it.
These two outsiders are threatening me, Ikaron. Even tails over there!
And you! Stay out of my pockets!
You little split-tongued freak!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: |Raising a fist to hit the kid.|

Text.Value: If his parents won't do it, I will.
Hand it over or I'll slap the teeth out of your head.
You don't scare me.
You don't understand! The kid stole my locket! He... aw, the hells with this.
Him, I'll hit once. You won't be so lucky. Get out of the way.
You godsdamned snake!

Text.Value: Guards! Help me!
Keep quiet and watch.
Relax. The boy's good, but I'm better - here's your locket.
You're lying. I see it in your face.
Just take the damn thing and leave me alone!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Holding the amulet back, furious and sad. Wet eyes but not crying.

Text.Value: You'll get yours some day. I hope I get to see it.
Child, you promised to stop stealing. You disgrace us all. Give it back.
What's happening here?
See you around.
Poor kid.

Synopsis:
Non-critpath. A human adventurer accuses a tiefling child of stealing a necklace from him. A tiefling guard may intervene if things get out of hand. 

Barth: Angry, but gruff and restrained. 
Meli: Fearless, urging Barth on.
